Round 1: Core Java (Fundamentals Round)
1. == vs .equals()
== → checks reference (memory address)
.equals() → checks logical equality

👉 What they test:
Do you understand object memory & references

2. wait() vs sleep()

Typical hidden expectations:

wait():
Releases lock
Used in synchronization
sleep():
Does NOT release lock
Just pauses thread

👉 What they test:

Thread lifecycle understanding
Synchronization behavior
3. HashMap Internals

You’re expected to know:

Buckets + hashing
Collision handling (LinkedList → Tree after threshold)
Load factor & resizing

👉 What they test:

Not usage, but internal working
4. hashCode() & equals()
If .equals() is overridden → must override hashCode()
Otherwise → broken behavior in HashMap/HashSet

👉 What they test:

Real-world bugs understanding


